Integer.Name: PayloadSize
Integer.ToolTip: Expected size of buffers for the data stream
Integer.Description: Expected size of buffers for the data stream. This depends on the camera resolution, onboard pixel processing (e.g., UnpackingMode, BayerMethod), padding (Pitch[DataStream], StripePitch). Also depends on BufferPartCount (area-scan firmware variants) and BufferHeight (line-scan firmware variants).

EnumEntry.Description: Enable latency compensation for StartOfScan events only.

EnumEntry.Name: EnableForEndOfScanOnly
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Enable latency compensation for EndOfScan events only
EnumEntry.Description: Enable latency compensation for EndOfScan events only.

EnumEntry.ToolTip: DMA operations are optimized for low latency and maximum PCIe throughput
EnumEntry.Description: DMA operations are optimized for low latency and maximum PCIe throughput.

EnumEntry.Name: LowMemoryUsage
EnumEntry.ToolTip: DMA operations are optimized for low memory usage; this may lead to higher latency and reduced PCIe throughput
EnumEntry.Description: DMA operations are optimized for low memory usage; this may lead to higher latency and reduced PCIe throughput.

Integer.Name: DmaEngineMaxQueueSize
Integer.ToolTip: Maximum number of pending buffers (i.e., buffers queued for DMA operations)
Integer.Description: Maximum number of pending buffers (i.e., buffers queued for DMA operations). Pending buffers are removed from the input queue and placed in an internal pending buffer queue. When a pending buffer is filled, it is removed from the pending buffer queue and placed in the output buffer queue. Higher values of DmaEngineMaxQueueSize lead to lower latency and higher PCIe throughput. DmaEngineMaxQueueSize is ignored when DmaEngineOptimization is set to LowMemoryUsage.

Integer.Name: BufferPartCount
Integer.ToolTip: Number of images to put in one buffer (default: 1)
Integer.Description: Number of images to put in one buffer (default: 1). Using larger values is recommended for high frame rate applications. Note that the value of BufferPartCount is only used when the buffer is announced.

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentSize
Integer.ToolTip: Segment size in bytes defines the transfer size
Integer.Description: Segment size in bytes defines the transfer size.

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentOffset
Integer.ToolTip: Segment offset in bytes
Integer.Description: Segment offset in bytes defines the transfer destination offset from the base address of the announced buffer or part (-1 to discard the data). The program keeps track of the transfer destination offset of each segment individually in the sequence.

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentOffsetIncrement
Integer.ToolTip: Segment offset increment in bytes
Integer.Description: Segment offset increment in bytes defines the signed transfer destination offset automatic increment (ignored when DmaSegmentOffset is -1). The program keeps track of each segment transfer destination offset incremented by DmaSegmentOffsetIncrement.

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentsActiveCount
Integer.ToolTip: Count of segments that are active in the cycle of DmaSegmentsCycleCount steps
Integer.Description: DmaSegmentsActiveCount defines the count of active steps (that is allowed to transfer data) in a cycle of DmaSegmentsCycleCount steps. DmaSegmentsActiveCount=1 with DmaSegmentsCycleCount=1 means that all segments are active but DmaSegmentsActiveCount=1 with DmaSegmentsCycleCount=2 means that only one out of two segments is active. An internal cycle step counter is used to decide when a segment is active or not, this counter is incremented on every segment and it is not reset when the sequence of segments is repeated but only after the repeat count (DmaSegmentsRepeatCount).

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentsCycleCount
Integer.ToolTip: Count of segments defining an independent cycle in the repeated sequence of segments
Integer.Description: DmaSegmentsCycleCount defines the total count of steps defining a cycle. This feature is used with DmaSegmentsActiveCount. DmaSegmentsActiveCount=1 with DmaSegmentsCycleCount=1 means that all segments are active but DmaSegmentsActiveCount=1 with DmaSegmentsCycleCount=2 means that only one out of two segments is active. An internal cycle step counter is used to decide when a segment is active or not, this counter is incremented on every segment and it is not reset when the sequence of segments is repeated but only after the repeat count (DmaSegmentsRepeatCount).

Integer.Name: DmaSegmentsRepeatCount
Integer.ToolTip: Segments repeat count
Integer.Description: Segments repeat count defines the number of times the sequence of segments is repeated. The cycle step counter is only reset after the repeat count (DmaSegmentsRepeatCount).

Command.Name: DmaAddSequence
Command.ToolTip: Add a new sequence of segments defined by DmaSegmentsRepeatCount, DmaSegmentsActiveCount and DmaSegmentsCycleCount to the selected program
Command.Description: Add a new sequence of segments defined by DmaSegmentsRepeatCount, DmaSegmentsActiveCount and DmaSegmentsCycleCount to the selected program.
